This paper deals with lower bounds on the amortized cost of operations in heap data structures, which is a classic topic in data structures research. The paper specifically focuses on the pure heap model, which is a well-studied model in this area. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves some analysis of the complexity of the decrease-key operation, which could fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.AL (Computational Complexity). The paper uses techniques from information theory, which could also place it in cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves some discussion of augmented data structures, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
